The solution iterates through the string from the last character to the first character (n - 1 to 0) and for each iteration, it creates a temporary StringBuilder to store the substring from the next character to the current character. After that, it reverses the temporary StringBuilder and appends it to the main result StringBuilder. Finally, it reverses the result StringBuilder and returns the last substring in lexicographical order. This approach has a time complexity of O(n) and a space complexity of O(n), making it efficient for solving the problem.

